text: Haut-Nkam is a department of West Province in Cameroon. The size of the department is 958 km, and as of 2005, there were 191,600 people living there. The capital of the department is at Bafang. == Subdivisions == The department is run by 7 communes, which are in turn made up of towns. * Bana * Bafang (urban) * Bafang (rural) * Bandja * Banka * Bakou * Batcheu == References == Category:Pages with unreviewed translations Category:Geography of Cameroon
